@startuml
title Use Case 1: Profile Creation and Login

actor User
participant LoginScreen
participant AccountManager
participant UserDB
database Database

== Register ==

User -> LoginScreen : enter username & password
User -> LoginScreen : click Register
LoginScreen -> AccountManager : register(username, password)

AccountManager -> UserDB  : check if username exists
UserDB  -> Database : search username
Database --> UserDB  : result
UserDB  --> AccountManager : username found / not found

alt Username not found
    AccountManager -> UserDB  : save new user
    UserDB  -> Database : insert new record
    AccountManager --> LoginScreen : show success message
else Username already exists
    AccountManager --> LoginScreen : show error message
end

== Login ==

User -> LoginScreen : enter username & password
User -> LoginScreen : click Login
LoginScreen -> AccountManager : login(username, password)

AccountManager -> UserDB  : get user by username
UserDB  -> Database : search user
Database --> UserDB  : user record
UserDB  --> AccountManager : user record

alt Information is correct
    AccountManager --> LoginScreen : login successful
else Information is incorrect
    AccountManager --> LoginScreen : show error message
end

@enduml